Here's how you can implement this in Julia. Please note that we can not perform statistical analysis on an empty data list. Thus, for an empty dataset, the function will return NamedTuple with all fields as `nothing`. 

```julia
using Statistics: mean, maximum, minimum

function weather_data_analyzer(temps)
    if isempty(temps)
        return (average=nothing, max=nothing, min=nothing, trend=nothing)
    else
        average = mean(temps)
        maxTemp = maximum(temps)
        minTemp = minimum(temps)

        if temps[1] > temps[2] 
            return (average=average, max=maxTemp, min=minTemp, trend=:decreasing)
        elseif temps[1] < temps[2]
            return (average=average, max=maxTemp, min=minTemp, trend=:increasing)
        else 
            return (average=average, max=maxTemp, min=minTemp, trend=:stable)
        end
    end
end
```
